## Object-Oriented Programming

### 1. Classes & Objects
```java
public class Car {
    private String color;

    public Car(String color) { this.color = color; }
    public void drive() { System.out.println("Driving..."); }
}

Car car = new Car("Red");
car.drive();
```

### 2. Encapsulation
Hide data using private fields + public getters/setters.
```java
private int age;
public int getAge() { return age; }
public void setAge(int age) { if (age > 0) this.age = age; }
```

### 3. Inheritance
Child inherits from parent using `extends`.
```java
public class Dog extends Animal {
    @Override
    public void eat() { System.out.println("Dog eats"); }
}
```

### 4. Polymorphism
**Overloading** (compile-time): Same method, different parameters
```java
public int add(int a, int b) { return a + b; }
public double add(double a, double b) { return a + b; }
```

**Overriding** (runtime): Child overrides parent method
```java
Animal dog = new Dog();
dog.eat();  // Calls Dog's eat()
```

### 5. Abstraction & Interfaces
```java
public abstract class Shape {
    public abstract double getArea();
}

public interface Animal {
    void eat();
}

public class Dog implements Animal {
    @Override public void eat() { }
}
```

### 6. this & super Keywords
- `this`: Current object reference
- `super`: Parent class reference

## Control Flow

### if-else & switch
```java
if (age >= 18) {
    System.out.println("Adult");
} else {
    System.out.println("Minor");
}

switch(day) {
    case 1: System.out.println("Mon"); break;
    case 2: System.out.println("Tue"); break;
    default: System.out.println("Other");
}
```

### Ternary
```java
String status = (age >= 18) ? "Adult" : "Minor";
```

### Loops
```java
// For
for (int i = 0; i < 5; i++) { System.out.println(i); }

// For-each
for (int num : arr) { System.out.println(num); }

// While
while (i < 5) { i++; }

// Do-while
do { i++; } while (i < 5);
```

### break & continue
```java
for (int i = 0; i < 10; i++) {
    if (i == 5) break;      // Exit
    if (i == 2) continue;   // Skip
}
```

### Logical Operators
- `&&` (AND), `||` (OR), `!` (NOT)
- Comparison: `==`, `!=`, `>`, `<`, `>=`, `<=`

## Arrays

### Declaration & Initialization
```java
int[] arr = new int[5];        // Size 5
int[] arr = {1, 2, 3};         // Literal
int value = arr[0];            // Access
int len = arr.length;          // Length
```

### 2D Arrays
```java
int[][] matrix = new int[3][3];
int[][] matrix = {{1, 2}, {3, 4}};

for (int i = 0; i < matrix.length; i++) {
    for (int j = 0; j < matrix[i].length; j++) {
        System.out.println(matrix[i][j]);
    }
}
```

### Arrays Utility
```java
Arrays.sort(arr);       // Sort
Arrays.binarySearch(arr, 5);  // Search
Arrays.fill(arr, 0);   // Fill
Arrays.copyOf(arr, len);  // Copy
Arrays.equals(arr1, arr2);  // Compare
```

## Strings

### Creation & Common Methods
```java
String str = "Hello";  // Literal
String str = new String("Hello");  // Object

str.length();  str.charAt(0);  str.substring(0, 3);
str.toUpperCase();  str.toLowerCase();  str.trim();
str.equals("Hello");  str.compareTo("Hi");
str.indexOf('l');  str.contains("ell");  str.split(" ");
```

## Collections

### List (Ordered, duplicates allowed)
```java
List<String> list = new ArrayList<>();
list.add("Apple");  list.add("Banana");
list.add(1, "Orange");  // Insert at index

String first = list.get(0);
list.remove(0);  list.remove("Apple");
boolean exists = list.contains("Banana");
int size = list.size();

for (String item : list) { System.out.println(item); }
```

### Set (Unordered, no duplicates)
```java
Set<String> set = new HashSet<>();
set.add("Apple");  set.add("Apple");  // Ignored

Set<Integer> sorted = new TreeSet<>();  // Sorted
```

### Map (Key-Value pairs)
```java
Map<String, Integer> map = new HashMap<>();
map.put("Apple", 5);
Integer value = map.get("Apple");
map.containsKey("Banana");
map.remove("Apple");

for (String key : map.keySet()) { System.out.println(key); }
for (Map.Entry<String, Integer> e : map.entrySet()) {
    System.out.println(e.getKey() + ": " + e.getValue());
}

Map<Integer, String> sorted = new TreeMap();  // Sorted
```

### Queue
```java
Queue<Integer> queue = new PriorityQueue<>();
queue.add(5);  queue.add(2);  queue.add(8);
while (!queue.isEmpty()) {
    System.out.println(queue.poll());  // 2 5 8
}
```

### Collections Utility
```java
Collections.sort(list);  Collections.reverse(list);
Collections.shuffle(list);  Collections.min(list);
Collections.max(list);  Collections.frequency(list, 5);
```

## Exception Handling

### Exception Hierarchy
- **Checked**: IOException, SQLException (must catch/declare)
- **Unchecked**: NullPointerException, ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException
- **Error**: StackOverflowError, OutOfMemoryError

### try-catch-finally
```java
try {
    int result = 10 / 0;  // Throw
} catch (ArithmeticException e) {
    System.out.println("Error: " + e.getMessage());
    e.printStackTrace();
} finally {
    System.out.println("Always executes");
}
```

### Multi-catch (Java 7+)
```java
try {
    // Code
} catch (NullPointerException | ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException e) {
    System.out.println("Caught");
}
```

### try-with-resources (Java 7+)
```java
try (FileReader fr = new FileReader("file.txt")) {
    // Use resource
} catch (IOException e) {
    // Handle
}  // Auto-closed
```

### throw & throws
```java
// throw: Manual exception
if (age < 0) throw new IllegalArgumentException("Invalid");

// throws: Declare exception
public void readFile(String name) throws IOException {
    FileReader fr = new FileReader(name);
}
```

### Custom Exception
```java
public class InvalidAgeException extends Exception {
    public InvalidAgeException(String msg) { super(msg); }
}

throw new InvalidAgeException("Age must be 18+");
```

### Common Exceptions
| Exception | Cause |
|-----------|-------|
| NullPointerException | null access |
| ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException | Invalid index |
| ArithmeticException | Division by zero |
| NumberFormatException | Invalid string to number |

## Multithreading

### Creating Threads

**Extend Thread**
```java
public class MyThread extends Thread {
    @Override
    public void run() {
        for (int i = 0; i < 5; i++) {
            System.out.println("Thread " + i);
            try { Thread.sleep(1000); } catch (InterruptedException e) {}
        }
    }
}

MyThread t = new MyThread();
t.start();  // NOT run()
```

**Implement Runnable** (Preferred)
```java
Thread t = new Thread(() -> System.out.println("Running"));
t.start();
```

### Thread Methods
```java
thread.start();    // Start
thread.join();     // Wait for completion
Thread.sleep(1000);  // Sleep
thread.setName("Worker");  // Set name
thread.setPriority(10);  // Priority 1-10
thread.isAlive();  // Check status
```

### Synchronization
```java
// Synchronized method
public synchronized void increment() { count++; }

// Synchronized block
synchronized(lock) { count++; }
```

### wait() & notify()
```java
public synchronized void produce() throws InterruptedException {
    while (data != null) wait();
    data = "value";
    notifyAll();
}
```

### volatile Keyword
```java
private volatile boolean flag = true;  // Visible to all threads
```

### Executor Framework
```java
ExecutorService executor = Executors.newFixedThreadPool(3);
for (int i = 0; i < 5; i++) {
    executor.execute(() -> System.out.println("Task"));
}
executor.shutdown();
```

### Callable & Future
```java
Future<Integer> future = executor.submit(() -> 42);
try {
    Integer result = future.get();  // Blocks
} catch (ExecutionException | InterruptedException e) {}
```

### ConcurrentHashMap
```java
ConcurrentHashMap<String, Integer> map = new ConcurrentHashMap<>();
map.put("key", 100);  // Thread-safe
```
